{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"30a4793d-f3f5-43b9-9745-50e5cb3dff26","content":"The directory appears empty, so I'll answer from general knowledge.\n\n## Migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n**1. Update your test project (`.csproj`):**\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Enable the new test platform runner -->\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nMake sure you're on **MSTest 3.x+** (SDK-style: `<UseMSTest>true</UseMSTest>`).\n\n**2. Replace `VSTest@3` in your pipeline YAML:**\n\n```yaml\n# Before\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**\\*Tests.dll'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# After\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n```\n\n**3. Publish results & coverage:**\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n> If you use **Coverlet** for cross-platform coverage instead of the VS collector, change `--collect` to `--collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"` and the summary format is already Cobertura.\n\n**Key differences:**\n- Tests now run via `dotnet test` (the new platform is invoked automatically).\n- TRX and coverage are handled via `--logger` and `--collect` arguments.\n- Results are published with separate pipeline tasks instead of being built into VSTest.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d1a804c9-d997-49ee-a7d9-76ab0d33d0e9","outputTokens":507,"requestId":"285A:33E26A:1594E1E:16FA25B:6A045FD6"},"id":"77ec9faf-bda5-4bfa-955a-0bd584fa005d","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:26:27.073Z","parentId":"efdeee51-6f5b-4ec7-ba0e-8835ee4b35eb"}
